Printing can be a challenge, I added a quick look version in the gallery  
With this openscad script  
d=10;  
union() {<br />
sphere(100);<br />
for (i=[1:25]) {<br />
rotate(rands(0,180,1)[0],[1,0,0]) {<br />
rotate(rands(0,180,1)[0],[0,1,0]) {<br />
difference() {<br />
cylinder(h=d,r=rands(100,110,1)[0]);<br />
cylinder(h=d,r=100);<br />
}<br />
}<br />
}<br />
}<br />
}  
Next I used opensketch to cut the lower half away, and to cut the cube underneath the semisphere again in two
